ἐ 78. cuiue, ‘the husband of any of them'; there is no necessity to change cuz'ui⁶ to communis with Geel, or to rewrite (with Jeep) cum est coniunx earum uix mortuus. The desire to alter cuius is due to a misunderstanding of mulieres, which refers, not to a group of women married to a particular man, but to the married women of India, each of whom was the wife of some man.
